[2] Cameroon: diagnosis
Date: 15 Dec 2010
From: Rob Reeder <r.reeder@cabi.org> [edited]


Re: taro disease in Cameroon, ProMED-mail post 20100715.2365
-----------------------------------
For the moment, we can say that the preliminary DNA sequence analysis
using the ITS region [internal transcribed spacer region, routinely
used to examine relationships among races of _Phytophthora_ - Mod.DHA]
shows more than 99 percent matches to the _Phytophthora
colocasiae_/_P. citrophthora_ species aggregate. We are continuing our
analysis in an effort to separate these closely related species.

--
Dr Robert Reeder
Deputy Head, Global Plant Clinic
CABI Europe - UK
<http://www.cabi.org>
